The coronavirus isolation unit at Tygerberg Hospital in Cape Town, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's coronavirus death toll has risen to 86. On Saturday night, the Department of Health announced that seven more people have died of COVID-19 in the country. The new deaths are from the Eastern Cape (4), Western Cape (2) and Limpopo (1). The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 4, 361. READ: Malls becoming COVID-19 health hazards The Western Cape remains the epicentre with more infections and deaths. With 1,514 infections, it leads followed by Gauteng and KwaZulu Natal with 1,304 and 847 respectively. The total number of tests conducted to date is 161, 004, of which 8, 614 were done in the last 24 hours. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.